    "summary": "Akeneo exposes a PIM GraphQL API, a hosted MCP server, a Supplier Data Manager REST API with an OpenAPI spec, and an Activation REST API; its PIM REST API is documented publicly and has a catalog-known OpenAPI spec URL, but that spec could not be accepted by the recorder tool.",
    "description": "Akeneo provides product information management and related product experience tools, including Product Cloud, Supplier Data Manager, and activation capabilities for commerce channels. Its platform helps organizations manage, enrich, and distribute product data across systems and channels.",
    "credentials": {
      "pim_connection": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Akeneo PIM connection credentials (client ID, client secret, API username, API password)",
        "generateUrl": "https://api.akeneo.com/documentation/authentication.html#client-idsecret-generation",
        "setup": "In your Akeneo PIM, go to `Connect > Connection settings`, click `Create`, save the connection, then open its `Credentials` section to copy the `client ID` and `secret`. Akeneo also generates an API `username` and `password` for that connection. See [REST API authentication](https://api.akeneo.com/documentation/authentication.html#client-idsecret-generation) and [API user creation](https://api.akeneo.com/documentation/authentication.html#api-user-creation)."
      },
      "pim_app_token": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Akeneo App access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://api.akeneo.com/apps/authentication-and-authorization.html",
        "setup": "Create/register an app and complete Akeneo's OAuth 2.0 authorization flow to obtain a permanent app access token. Start from [Apps authentication and authorization](https://api.akeneo.com/apps/authentication-and-authorization.html); Akeneo also provides a walkthrough at [How to get your App token](https://api.akeneo.com/tutorials/how-to-get-your-app-token.html)."
      },
      "sdm_api_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Supplier Data Manager API token",
        "generateUrl": "https://sdm.akeneo.cloud/api/v1/auth/token/",
        "setup": "Use your Supplier Data Manager user account to mint an API token by calling `POST https://sdm.akeneo.cloud/api/v1/auth/token/` with your account `email`, `password`, and a `token_name`. The response returns the token `key`. This flow is documented in [Supplier Data Manager API getting started](https://api.akeneo.com/supplier-data-manager/getting-started.html#step-1-get-your-token)."
      }
    },
